Commentary Text: Jadeja to Shubman Gill, out Stumped!! Dhoni is confident that he's got Gill here. The stumping appeal is sent upstairs, and sure enough, Gill is short of his ground. Lightning work with the gloves from Dhoni who's showing no signs of slowing down. Flat length ball around off, Gill stretches forward to drive but it turns away sharply past the edge. His back foot gets dragged out of the crease, and he has no chance of getting back with Dhoni in top form. The ball nestling into his gloves, and the stumps being broken almost happens simultaneously - that's how quick he is. Never ceases to amaze. Shubman Gill st Dhoni b Jadeja 39(20) [4s-7]

Commentary Text: Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, FOUR, CSK CHAMPIONS!! Can you believe it?? This was a low full toss on the pads, Jadeja with a wiggle inwards and just a gentle tickle to the left of short fine. Runs away for four, nobody could stop that. Jadeja runs to his captain, and then is off on a celebratory run around the stadium, his other CSK teammates try to catch up with him.... Scenes of sheer joy, all those in yellow celebrate, they breathe a sigh of relief. Chin up, Mohit Sharma. That was a top quality last over, but not to be his night...
